Business Overview:

The Equity Derivatives Structuring (Americas) is a multi-disciplinary team, centrally positioned within Global Markets Americas.
 
 The Equity Derivatives Structuring Structuring team focuses on:
 
 • Pricing, designing and transacting in financial derivatives, including advanced derivatives, as well as Quantitative Investment strategies and specific wrappers (swaps, structured notes, funds).

•Understanding market dynamics deeply with a view to find appealing investment strategies. Positioning those strategies with regards to market flows. Having a deep understanding of Exotics and Flow book positioning to understand how those strategies fit within the book.


 • Acting as derivatives product specialists and generating quantitative analyses to answer requests by salespeople, traders and clients on such products, or initiate product ideas with salespeople, traders and clients.
 
 • Researching designing and creating innovative derivatives products and quantitative investment strategies for clients.
 
 • Marketing and creating marketing materials to present such innovative derivatives products and quantitative investment strategies for clients.
 
 • Creating, programming and improving quantitative tools and software to perform the above structuring functions.
 
 • Collaborating closely with functions on business related to equity derivatives or quantitative financial products: credit risk, market risk, compliance, legal, marketing and other teams as needed.
 
• Client types serviced include: Hedge Funds, Asset Managers, Pensions / Endowments /Foundations, Insurance Companies, Distribution, Corporates, both in theAmericas and worldwide.
 
Candidate SuccessFactors:
Candidates are measured on the following four performance drivers, which will dictate how individual impact is considered on the Americas platform:

Results and Impact
Able to influence peers and team.
Demonstrates good judgement when making decisions of high complexity and impact.
Exercise appropriate autonomy in the execution and delivery of work. 
Responsible for driving outcomes, which have meaningful effect on team or department.
Leadership and Collaboration:
Creates trust with colleagues.
Acts in leadership capacity for projects, processes, or programs.
Client, Customer and Stakeholder Focus: 
Able to build relationships with a mix of colleagues and clients.
Interacts regularly with management and department leaders.
Demonstrates the ability to influence stakeholders at the team level. 
Compliance Culture and Conduct: 
Takes full responsibility for personal actions and demonstrates courage in facing problems and conflicts.
Perceived as a person of high moral character; upholds corporate values and displays high ethical standards.
Responsibilities: 
The successful candidate at the Vice President level will have a strong focus on the structuring of financial instruments with a primary focus on Complex Flow. The candidate will have a deep understanding on Equity Derivatives ecosystem and have a proven track record of deep technical understanding.

The candidate will design solutions, negotiate their pricing, represent them fairly to hedge fund portfolio managers, asset managers, pension fund managers.


 
Minimum Required Qualifications:
· At least 4year experience in Equity Derivatives Structuring,

· Strong technical skills including high proficiency with PowerPoint, Excel, and VBA.
 
 · Strong coding& programming skills in languages such as Python, R and/or Matlab.
 
 · Thorough understanding of financial derivatives and stochastic calculus.
 
 · Strong Science or Engineering background, preferably Master's Degree in a quantitative or business relevant field.
 
 ·  Experience financial modeling, quantitative finance, and statistical analysis of financial data.
 
 · Multi-tasking skills.
 
 · Ability to quickly respond to issues under pressure.
 
 · Strong analytical skills and attention to detail.
 
 · Strong interpersonal and communication skills.
 
 · Strong interest in Finance, Financial Markets, and Quantitative Finance.
 
 
Preferred Qualifications: 
· High GPA.
 
 · Knowledge of Financial Econometrics.
 
 · Knowledge of Machine Learning and Pattern Recognition.
 
 · Knowledge of Bloomberg, Reuters / Refinitiv or similar market data tool.
 
 

